Hi Guys

I have Transonic PNA6000T with Navigon 5.2.
Is it possible to upgrade it to versin 6 with this update and use the MN6 maps from here (TPB).

I am a newbie in this area, if possible could anyone post a short instruction.

Thanks a lot.

Instruction for updating Transonic PNA6000 from MN5.2 to this MN6 version:

1. Download this torrent. Extract the ZIP-archive.

2. Copy all the files to a SD-card. I used a 1Gb SD. After that moment, it'll be a MN6-folder with files and subfolders, and two ROOT-files (MNAVDCE.CAB and AUTORUNCE.EXE) on the SD-card. I use an USB Multicard-reader to copy files and folders directly to the SD-card from my HDD.

3. Download the Nordics_MN60.map as shown above in the forum. Copy this mapfile in the ROOT of the SD-card too. Although it is originally for PDAs, it works fine with the PNA too. I seems that PDA and PNA mapfiles are the same.

4. Place this SD-card in your PNA6000, and turn the ON/OFF hardware-switch in the bottom to OFF. Then turn it to ON again.

5. Start the PNA, and the upgrade process starts. Choose the language you want. I chose SWE, and it works 100%.

Good Luck!
